Responsive evaluation is a research based on reliable evidence of quality program. This approach enables to evaluate the educational and other programs by comparing the program activity, the program uniqueness, and the social plurality of the people.
The most important feature in the Responsive evaluation is the responsiveness to main issues and problems, in particular those cases where people recognize at the site.
The Responsive evaluation emphasizes:
Educational problems more than objectives or hypotheses
Direct and indirect observation of program participation (the pluralism of value standards held by various groups)
A continuous attention to audience information-needs and media for reporting
In order to achieve a well Responsive evaluation, it is essential to preordinate the evaluation.
